advance xpath:
get to the nearest sibling, parent or ancestor first and then have access to desired tag

following sibling:
//label[@name='myid']/following-sibling::input
hey get to tag name label whose attribute name has value "myid" and then get me its following
sibling which is "input"


preceding -sibling:
//input[@id='calFromDate']/preceding-sibling::label

parent:
//label[text()='enter message']
/parent::div

ancestor:
//label[text()="enter message']/ancestor::form

